HEADWORD: Edingtonite
<hw>Ed"ing*ton*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A grayish white zeolitic mineral, in tetragonal crystals. It is a
hydrous silicate of alumina and baryta.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

